<p>I'm trying to calculate PDF probability function of Image by means of Parzen windows, but I don't understand because the result for each pixel value is the same. I try to explain better, I choose width of parzen window and window function is a gaussian function, so PDF formula is :</p>  <p>d=1; h=delta;</p>  <p><a href="https://isrishblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/k2.jpg" rel="nofollow">gaussian window function</a> My Matlab code is:</p>  <p><code></p>  <pre><code>X=rand(20);   function pdf=parzen(X,dim,delta) pdf=zeros(20);    for u=0:dim-2            for v=0:dim-2                 for a=1+(u*dim):dim+(u*dim)                      for b=1+(v*dim):dim+(v*dim)                          for i=1+(u*dim):dim+(u*dim)                             for j=1+(v*dim):dim+(v*dim)                                ris=gaussianWindow((X(i,j)-X(a,b)),delta);                                  pdf(a,b)=pdf(a,b)+ris;                             end                          end                            pdf(a,b)=pdf(a,b)/(dim*dim);                      end                 end            end    end  end   function result=gaussianWindow(val,delta)     result=(1/(delta*sqrt(2*pi)))*exp(double((-val*val))/(2*delta*delta)); end </code></pre>  <p></code></p>  <p>Can you help me, please????</p>